hdiutil resize: resize partition or image
Usage:	hdiutil resize <sizespec> <image>
	Size specifiers:
	    -size < ?? | ??b | ??k | ??m | ??g | ??t | ??p | ??e | min >
	        (bytes, blocks, kilobytes, megabytes, gigabytes, terabytes, petabytes, exabytes)
	    -sectors <sector count>
		min		minimum size

	Resize options:
	    -imageonly		only change image file size
	    -partitiononly	only change the partition size

	    -partitionID <ID>		resize partition with given <ID>

	    -growonly		only allow image to grow
	    -shrinkonly		only allow image to shrink
	    -nofinalgap		allow complete elimination of trailing unallocated blocks for Apple Partition Maps

	    -limits		for given options, don't resize, just print default min/current/max sizes
	    -alllimits		for given options, don't resize, just list resize information for the image and all (any) partitions.

	Common options:
	    -encryption <crypto method>
	    	AES-128 - 128-bit AES encryption (recommended)
	    	AES-256 - 256-bit AES encryption (more secure, but slower)
	    -stdinpass
	    -agentpass
	    -srcimagekey <key>=<value>	(-imagekey is a synonym)
	    -shadow <shadowfile>
	    -insecurehttp
	    -cacert <file | dir>
	    -plist
	    -verbose
	    -debug
	    -quiet
